# PURPOSE:
#   Provide stable device names and permissions for serial devices, cameras, sensors, etc.
# STEPS:
# - Match devices by vendor/product/serial.
# - Create persistent symlinks under /dev/kitt/*.
# - Adjust MODE/GROUP so the service user (pi) can access without root.
#
# EXAMPLES (pseudocode; replace IDs with real values using `udevadm info -a -n /dev/ttyUSB0`):
#
# USB Serial adapter for EX-CommandStation (example IDs):
# SUBSYSTEM=="tty", ATTRS{idVendor}=="1a86", ATTRS{idProduct}=="7523", SYMLINK+="kitt/csb1-serial", MODE="0660", GROUP="dialout"
#
# Load cell ADC USB interface (example):
# SUBSYSTEM=="hidraw", ATTRS{idVendor}=="16c0", ATTRS{idProduct}=="0483", SYMLINK+="kitt/scale0", MODE="0660", GROUP="plugdev"
#
# CSI/USB Camera (example):
# SUBSYSTEM=="video4linux", ATTRS{idVendor}=="046d", ATTRS{idProduct}=="0825", SYMLINK+="kitt/cam0", MODE="0660", GROUP="video"
#
# After editing:
#   sudo udevadm control --reload
#   sudo udevadm trigger
